Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Thinly slice @jalapeño{1}(thinly sliced) into rounds, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). Dice @tomato{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces).

Toss cauliflower on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{3%teaspoon}, 2 tsp @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on top rack until cauliflower is tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While cauliflower roasts, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce} and season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine jalapeño, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, juice from half the lime, and a pinch of salt.

Microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a small #pot{} over medium heat. Add scallion whites, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and remaining fajita spice blend; cook, stirring, until scallion whites are softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender and water has evaporated, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Remove jalapeño from pickling liquid (reserve liquid). Reserve a few rounds for garnish; mince remaining jalapeño.

In a second small #bowl{}, combine cilantro, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, remaining garlic powder, a squeeze of lime juice, a big pinch of lime zest, and a pinch of minced jalapeño to taste.

> TIP: If you'd like more zesty heat, add a small splash of jalapeño pickling liquid instead of, or in addition to, lime juice.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a fork. Stir in tomato, a squeeze of lime juice, and as much remaining minced jalapeño as you like. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls; top with cauliflower. Drizzle everything with salsa verde. Garnish with reserved jalapeño rounds and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve.

Stir turkey or beef into rice along with tomato.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.